# =============================================================================
# Database Package — Local Environment Variables Template
#
# This package wraps Prisma + Neon PostgreSQL.
# In the monorepo the DATABASE_URL is defined in the root .env file and
# referenced here via dotenv-expand. You only need a separate value here
# if you want the database package to connect to a different database than
# the rest of the services (e.g. a dedicated migration user).
#
# Setup:
#   cp packages/database/.env.example packages/database/.env
# =============================================================================


# ── Database Connection String ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Aiven PostgreSQL (free tier): https://aiven.io
#   Create a project → Connection Details → copy the "Pooled connection" string.
#   Format: postgresql://<user>:<password>@<host>/<db>?sslmode=require
#
# In most cases you can simply reference the root .env variable:
DATABASE_URL="gdjfnfknjdogngkhmhign"
DATABASE_CA_CERTIFICATE="your-database-ca-certificate-in-base64"
